<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1051917-from-reading-the-synopsis-of-the-second">From reading the synopsis of the second book, it appears that these are all different characters? Not a true &quot;series&quot;? 

Thanks</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1051917'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F1936812.Night_Shift">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1051917-from-reading-the-synopsis-of-the-second">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1051917-from-reading-the-synopsis-of-the-second">Add your answer</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/25620126-jolayne"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1461084815i/25620126._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/25620126-jolayne">Jolayne</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Each story follows a different character, yes. However they all tie in, and you do get glimpses of the previous and future characters. I absolutely lo<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Each story follows a different character, yes. However they all tie in, and you do get glimpses of the previous and future characters. I absolutely loved the entire series. Each is similar to one another, but yet bring something different to the table. Very enjoyable reads, as Nora Roberts usually is. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
