  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3140873013" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3140873013" />
    <a title="latham" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/68089240-latham"><img alt="latham" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1626248428p2/68089240.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3140873013?book_show_action=true">Jan 28, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="latham" class="user" itemprop="url" name="latham" href="/user/show/68089240-latham">latham</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9780373073658" href="/book/show/712432.Night_Shift">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3140873013" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14877204500682360950">I had an unexpected level of fun reading this. It&apos;s the first Nora Roberts novel I&apos;ve read since The Witness, my first and only previous experience with her work.<br/><br/>And Night Shift was just so fun for me. <br/><br/>We follow Cilla, a radio show host, who, on air during request lines, starts being threatened with murder. The police become involved, namely Det. Boyd Fletcher, and a romance blooms between the two.<br/><br/>There&apos;s a certain level of drama to this one. Cilla really *really* does not want the police involv</span>
  <span id="freeText14877204500682360950" style="display:none">I had an unexpected level of fun reading this. It's the first Nora Roberts novel I've read since The Witness, my first and only previous experience with her work.<br /><br />And Night Shift was just so fun for me. <br /><br />We follow Cilla, a radio show host, who, on air during request lines, starts being threatened with murder. The police become involved, namely Det. Boyd Fletcher, and a romance blooms between the two.<br /><br />There's a certain level of drama to this one. Cilla really *really* does not want the police involved. I loved Cilla. Sure, her insistence that she didn't like Boyd and didn't need him/police/outsider help, got annoying after awhile. There's, however, a really well explored complexity to her actions. Deep levels of shame are slowly unraveled with the careful help of Boyd. Who, may not be the most interesting man on planet earth lol, was written with sincerity and, over time, a chemistry develops between the two. I believed he cared and wanted Cilla. It's a very dramatic and over the top relationship. Some eye-roll inducing dialogue but it was super fun. <br /><br />I liked the plot. It's a fine mystery, slightly creepy but not exactly suspenseful or well written. I loved the very 90s quality to it. The fact she's a hot popular radio host, for example. And that she's invited to play at events and shit. <br /><br />Night Shift is fun drama. A nice romance between some mostly well written characters and an engaging if not wholly interesting plot. <br /><br />7/10</span>
  <a data-text-id="14877204500682360950" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
