<span id="freeTextContainer4025759656483330954">An average story here - kind of a suspense romance. Cilla, the heroine is a DJ at a radio station getting threatening phone calls and the hero, Boyd Fletcher is the detective working her case...and working on getting her into bed. As is typically the case, Roberts writes a better hero than heroine. Boyd was just fine, a bit more alpha than I&apos;m used to seeing, but overall nice, determined and confident - he knows right away that he wants Cilla. She on the other hand is a mess. She&apos;s got all kind </span>
  <span id="freeText4025759656483330954" style="display:none">An average story here - kind of a suspense romance. Cilla, the heroine is a DJ at a radio station getting threatening phone calls and the hero, Boyd Fletcher is the detective working her case...and working on getting her into bed. As is typically the case, Roberts writes a better hero than heroine. Boyd was just fine, a bit more alpha than I'm used to seeing, but overall nice, determined and confident - he knows right away that he wants Cilla. She on the other hand is a mess. She's got all kind of baggage that makes her indecisive, a bit on the stupid side and her reasons for not wanting a relationship are just a bit over-stressed. She holds onto it way too long. Still, I was entertained, so it gets a 3. </span>
  <a data-text-id="4025759656483330954" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

