  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2545071015" />
    <a title="Regina Pride" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23146915-regina-pride"><img alt="Regina Pride" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/f_50x66-6a03a5c12233c941481992b82eea8d23.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2545071015?book_show_action=true">Sep 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Regina Pride" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Regina Pride" href="/user/show/23146915-regina-pride">Regina Pride</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2545071015" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7980472788509815060">Heretofore, I had intended to read more from Ms Roberts prolific expanse of series of books. Now, I&apos;m getting off the thought to do it, and putting it into action. This is the first book in her Night Tales series, and I thought it was good. They deal with a set of detectives and the overflow of the close people acquainted with them, such as their wives, partners, girlfriends, boyfriends, etc and stuff like that. I was surprised that Ms Roberts wrote stuff like this because I had mostly been acqu</span>
  <span id="freeText7980472788509815060" style="display:none">Heretofore, I had intended to read more from Ms Roberts prolific expanse of series of books. Now, I'm getting off the thought to do it, and putting it into action. This is the first book in her Night Tales series, and I thought it was good. They deal with a set of detectives and the overflow of the close people acquainted with them, such as their wives, partners, girlfriends, boyfriends, etc and stuff like that. I was surprised that Ms Roberts wrote stuff like this because I had mostly been acquainted with her more supernatural ones and her In Death series under J.D. Robb. I really like this type of writing from her. It has your cops, crime, good guys and of course, your romance. If you like these sort of things, find a Nora Roberts books dealing with cops and criminals.</span>
  <a data-text-id="7980472788509815060" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

