    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3606041746" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3606041746" />
    <a title="Elīna Zviedre" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/36594181-el-na-zviedre"><img alt="Elīna Zviedre" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1598274621p2/36594181.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3606041746?book_show_action=true">Oct 21, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elīna Zviedre" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elīna Zviedre" href="/user/show/36594181-el-na-zviedre">Elīna Zviedre</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3606041746" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17837844282436122043">The reason I picked up this series was because people started saying how similar it was to her In Death series. That this served as a blueprint for the gloriousness that came after and I have to say I could see that and I couldn&apos;t stop fangirling over it.<br/>Bag of candied almonds - Feeney<br/>Jasmine tea- Dr. Mira<br/>All the music references made me think of Mavis<br/>Not to mention a mix of characters that later made Eve and Roarke. <br/>With all that, this was a separate story in its own right. Cilla was a bit inno</span>
  <span id="freeText17837844282436122043" style="display:none">The reason I picked up this series was because people started saying how similar it was to her In Death series. That this served as a blueprint for the gloriousness that came after and I have to say I could see that and I couldn't stop fangirling over it.<br />Bag of candied almonds - Feeney<br />Jasmine tea- Dr. Mira<br />All the music references made me think of Mavis<br />Not to mention a mix of characters that later made Eve and Roarke. <br />With all that, this was a separate story in its own right. Cilla was a bit innocent and naive to the point where it got infuriating. I could feel Boyd's frustration perfectly. <br />How could she not have thought to mention a guy who stalked her for months is beyond me. In a police investigation every little detail counts. I get that she didn't want to talk about her mother and father getting killed but that is an important detail to mention when someone wants you dead. <br />Also, I didn't think that police put that much effort in questioning her or finding out who was stalking her. They only found out about this crazy guy from one of her rants. <br />That said, the investigative part was the weakest point in the story.<br />The romance, however, was a banger. Even if it got a bit cringey sometimes.<br />The whole deal about sex was very well executed in the terms of it really isn't only one person's fault if there is trouble in the bedroom. <br />Boyd was an absolute dream and delight. Only he could handle Cilla cause she really was a mess.<br />This was a very addictive read but I wished Cilla would have grown some balls. Also, I couldn't help but wish that she would have been the one to get hurt in the end. I feel like that would have given her a better perspective of how everything can happen in life and not just to the people she loves but to her as well. The reasons why she was scared being attached to someone working in a police force were valid but that didn't negate the fact that people who care about her couldn't be affected by her being in danger as well.<br />It got a bit repetitive and more often than not I got the sense Boyd was her bodyguard not a cop. Other than that I definitely enjoyed this one, especially considering that I've tried to steer clear from Nora Roberts books.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="17837844282436122043" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

