<div id="review_3440454769" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3440454769" />
    <a title="Sandra R" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/23874363-sandra-r"><img alt="Sandra R" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1595891382p2/23874363.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3440454769?book_show_action=true">Jul 13, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sandra R" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sandra R" href="/user/show/23874363-sandra-r">Sandra R</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/19054396-night-shift">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3440454769" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10429149397449935097">I was really enjoying reading this romance/suspense, but by about half way in, I wasn&apos;t liking Cilla much at all. Especially when it was revealed she&apos;d &apos;forgotten&apos; an incident that had only happened recently, so I think it was a bit of a plot hole. Something like that wouldn&apos;t have slipped my mind - let alone someone being stalked, so that&apos;s when I became disengaged with the story and pretty turned off the heroine. Loved her cop hero.<br/><br/>This book was originally published in 1991 and of course that </span>
  <span id="freeText10429149397449935097" style="display:none">I was really enjoying reading this romance/suspense, but by about half way in, I wasn't liking Cilla much at all. Especially when it was revealed she'd 'forgotten' an incident that had only happened recently, so I think it was a bit of a plot hole. Something like that wouldn't have slipped my mind - let alone someone being stalked, so that's when I became disengaged with the story and pretty turned off the heroine. Loved her cop hero.<br /><br />This book was originally published in 1991 and of course that shows and I was expecting that. It was quite nice to read a suspense set in the era before mobile phones and the internet - you know, no intricate technology in place to catch the bad guy etc. Threw me back to the past and I liked that. The description of the clothes had me chuckling as did some of the slang and the record turning and cassettes and the pay phone use. <br /><br />The romance was slow burn which I liked, then when it sped up it was sizzling, tasteful, steamy and very well written - as was the whole story. Believe it or not, this is the first book I have ever read by Nora Roberts/J.D. Robb. I'll be reading more. 3.5 stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10429149397449935097" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


